Video.Title: Why is an A1466 Macbook Pro taking 45-65 mA and not turning on?

Wiki.Notes: Added to wiki. My understanding is that if this chip (U1930) is bad, power draw may vary depending on which rail the bad chip takes down with it. Uncertain, so added under 'No power, 40-65mA power draw' since this is shown in the video. Added video link as example.
